          'question' => 'Is the 100 lire coin of 1955 rare?',
          'answer' => 'The 100 lire coins of 1955 aren\'t considered rare, due to the print run of  8 million six hundred thousand . The numismatic interest for this coin counts only for the copies in state of newly minted preservation. They are really difficult to find. In this case the commercial value can reach around 1200 euros.',
