            'alt' => '',
          ),
          'body' => 'We propose here a brief summary of coins that acquired particular approval and value also out of their borders, becoming coins of international interest.<br>

<br>

<b>The tetradrachm or Athenian Owl</b><br><b>The stater or "Pegasus" of Corinth</b><br><b>The tetradrachm of Alexander the Great</b><br><b>The roman denarius of republican era</b><br><b>The roman denarius of imperial era</b><br><b>The roman aureus</b><br><b>The byzantine solidus</b><br><b>The florin</b><br><b>The venetian ducat</b><br><b>The thaler</b><br><b><a href="__ROUTE:guide.leeuwenndaalder__">The leeuwenndaalder</a></b><br><b>The Spanish coin of 8 escudos</b><br><b>The Spanish coin of 8 reals</b><br><b>The dollar</b><br><b>The marengo</b><br><b>The écu of 5 Francs</b><br><b>The English Sovereign</b><br><b>The euro</b><br>

<i><br>Claudia Maresca<br>Francesca Barenghi<br>Umberto Moruzzi</i><i><br></i>',
